<TITLE> HDZ Transfusion</TITLE>

used without permission, for ``fair use" only
<hr>


<h1> HDZ Leaders Donate Blood</h1><p>

 
<h2><i> by A.Malenica<br>  Slobodna Dalmacija, 5/6/95, Split, Croatia</i></h2><p>


<hr>

ZAGREB - The leaders and members of the HDZ [Hrvatska Demokratska Zajednica, Croatian Democratic Union; Ruling party in Croatia] responded to the invitation by the Institute for Transfusionology by donating blood on the premises of the party's General Secretariat.  The drive for voluntary blood donations started at 8:30 and finished at 12:00;  during that time many parliamentarians as well as the members of the General Secretariat donated blood, also joined by the employees of the many companies whose offices are located nearby.<p>

The Secretary-General of the HDZ, Zlatko Canjuga, said that the HDZ organizes such drives every 2-3 months and that the latest one was, as he emphasized, the least the leadership of the HDZ could do regarding the serious situation in Croatia and Zagreb.<p> 

He also expressed satisfaction with the response of the HDZ members to this humanitarian action, emphasizing that it was a small part of the HDZ's contribution to the general situation. "This way, we'll help the Croatian defenders, policemen and civilians who were hurt in these savage Serbian attacks," concluded Canjuga.<p>


<hr>

Translated on 8/20/95

