<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Placer Dome - Lustrous Performer</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	
	<a href="#00">
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	
	<tr>
	
	<td valign=top>	
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/001head.jpg" alt="Lustrous Performer jpeg">
	<p>
		
	Throughout history, culture has accorded gold a special place. A
	product like no other, it is both commodity and financial asset. Gold is
	attractive to people for many reasons. A form of money, its owners
	can hold it, trade it, make loans on it or convert it to other financial
	instruments with relative ease. Its role as jewelry is inextricably rooted in

	<img src="../gfx/gold$$.jpg" alt="Wall Street jpeg" align=right vspace=10>

	cultures around the world. And increasingly, its commodity value is tied to its
	lustrous performance as a material in a wide range of applications.
	<p>
	
	<font size=+1>
	<strong>
	<a href="01a1.html">
	Healer, Hedge and Adornment</a>
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	While microscopic gold pellets fight cancer, gold-plated visors help men and women
	fight fires. Gold is also a versatile investment and personal adornment.
	<p>
	
	<font size=+1>
	<strong>
	<a href="01a2.html">
	Ancient Tombs of Gold</a>
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	As early as 4,000 BC, Egyptian pharoahs were buried with their gold, believing 
	they would require it in the after-life. 
	<p>
	
	<font size=+1>
	<strong>
	<a href="01a3.html">
	The Search for Supply</a>
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	The demand picture is extremely complex. Gold miners are
	somewhat more comfortable discussing supply.
	<p>
	
	<font size=+1>
	<strong>
	The Sidebars
	</strong>
	</font>	
	<p>

	<li><a href="01a5.html">Jewelry: Two-thirds of the World's Gold</a>
	<br>
	<li><a href="01a5.html#01">Know Your Karats</a>
	<br>
	<li><a href="01a4.html">History of Gold Repeats Itself</a>
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
	
	<td>	
	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
