<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Placer Dome - Investment in Talent</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/01butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/04head.gif" alt="The Profile header gif">
	<p>
	
	<table>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<img src="../gfx/mulamex.jpg" alt="Mulatos project jpeg" align=right hspace=10 vspace=5>

	Placer Dome Inc. is a publicly-owned company and its shares are widely
	distributed. On December 31, 1995 the Corporation had 239,090,103 shares
	outstanding and 19,110 shareholders of record. Of the shares outstanding,
	46.16% were registered in the United States, 52.27% in
	Canada and 1.57% elsewhere.
	<p>
	The Corporation was established in 1987 by the amalgamation of Placer
	Development Limited of Vancouver (incorporated in 1926), Dome Mines
	Limited (incorporated in 1910) and Campbell Red Lake Mines Limited
	(incorporated in 1944), both of Toronto. Placer Dome has interests in
	16 mines, 13 of them gold mines, located in Australia, Canada, Chile, Papua
	New Guinea and the United States. Two new mines start up in 1997 and a third,
	in Venezuela, starts in 1998. By the end of
	1995, the Corporation employed 8,000 people -- 1,000 more than in 1994.
	<p>
	
	<a href="04b.html">Mission Statement/Goals and Objectives</a><br>
	<a href="04c.html">Board of Directors</a><br>
	<a href="04d.html">Officers</a><br>
	<br><br>
	</td>
	
	<tr>
	<td>
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
