<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Explorers - New Mines for Old</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	<table border=0>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
		
	<td valign=top>
	
	<h2>
	Minex: New Mines for Old
	</h2>
	
	<a href="02a.html">
	Back to "Modern Day Explorers"</a>
	<p>
		
	"The best place to look for a new mine is in the shadow of an old headframe," as
	the saying goes.
	<p>

	<img src="../gfx/02minex.jpg" align=right alt="Kiena Mine headframe" hspace=10 vspace=5>

	Ore deposits are classified into one of several general types. However, within each deposit, unique geologic characteristics may be recognized,
	and these may determine the mode of occurrence, configuration and size for the 
	deposit. There may be signatures for potential satellites to the main deposit,
	and these possibilities then become the focus for exploration programmes on the 
	mine properties and adjoining areas.
	<p>
	These Minex programmes (exploration efforts at or adjacent to existing mine sites) were
	initiated with the objective of studying, evaluating and identifying potential
	expansions to known orebodies and finding new deposits on the mine properties. These
	programmes are coordinated between exploration geologists and mine geologists to fit
	both short- and long-term mine plans.
		<p>
	Here are some recent results of Placer Dome Minex activites:
	<p>
			
	<li type=bullet>In 1985, Australia's Kidston Mine reserves were estimated at 37 million
	tonnes, which would keep the mine running until 1995. By 1991, Minex had added 33
	million tonnes to initial reserves. Mine life has now been extended to 2003,
	because of the discovery of 57.13 million tonnes of ore since the mine went into
	production.
	<p>
	
	<li type=bullet>The new "QK Deposit Zone" was found at Detour Lake Mine in Canada in 1995, adding
	significant reserves.
	<p>
	
	<li type=bullet>The H.G Young prospect, a small past-producer on the Campbell property,
	is being investigated for further reserves.
	<p>
		
	<li type=bullet>20,000 metres of drilling on the Lamaque property (adjacent to the Sigma gold
	mine in Canada) has intersected  mineralized vein systems. Placer Dome
	is confident these new mineral intersections will become ore reserves.
	<p>
	
	
	<li type=bullet>At the Kiena gold mine in Canada, the "North Zone" has been upgraded. A 
	higher grade ore zone was also discovered in 1993 and is being further delineated
	this year.
	<p>
	
	
	<li type=bullet>Minex has led to success at two U.S. gold mines: Bald Mountain and the 
	Cortez Joint Venture.
	<p></td>
		
	</table>
		
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>
	
	<td width=120></td>
	
	
	<td>
	
	<center>	

