<HEAD>
<TITLE>Explorers - Rugged Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	<table border=0>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
		
	<td valign=top>
	
	<h2>
	The Rugged Office
	</h2>
	
	
	<a href="02a.html">
	Back to "Modern Day Explorers"</a>
	<p>

	<img src="../gfx/02office.jpg" align=right alt="La Coipa landscape" hspace=10 vspace=5>

	In remote locations across the planet, in Latin
	America, China, Singapore, Jakarta, Port Moresby, Ivory Coast, Mali and Russia,
	Placer Dome's exploration work continues day in, day out. How will
	convergent exploration technologies re-shape the reality of Placer Dome
	prospectors in the field? We can answer this question with a couple of words:
	"Rugged office."
	<p>
	

	Typically the project development sites (these include both exploration and 
	production properties) that require communications are not in cities...but 
	are located a considerable distance from built up areas. With that in mind,
	on the drawing boards at Placer Dome is an exciting and innovative mobile computing 
	"toolkit" designed to provide a combination of hardware, software and 
	connecting devices to PDI employees who travel, enabling them to do mobile
	computing.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	An office in a briefcase
	</strong>
	<p>

	
	Placer Dome's "rugged office" project must support easy-to-use voice and 
	data communication and support the capture and appropriate analysis of business
	information. Essentially it is an office in a briefcase, easily
	transportable and user-friendly.
	<p>


	<img src="../gfx/02rugged.jpg" align=right alt="Control systems" hspace=10 vspace=5>


	An "office in a briefcase" will provide Placer Dome explorationists with a number
	of advantages. It will allow geologists to exchange production, technical and
	business information worldwide. It will create an infrastructure in which raw data
	can be transmitted from remote field locations to be processed by specialists
	off-site. It will facilitate virtual meetings, eliminating the necessity for
	physical meetings which can be costly and difficult to orchestrate in
	far-flung locations.</td>

	</table>
	
	<p><br>
	
	
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>
	
	<td width=120></td>
	
	<td>
	
	<center>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
