<HEAD>
<TITLE>Performer - History of Gold</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a>
	<br>
		
	<table border=0>
	
	<tr>
	
	<td>
	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	History of Gold Repeats Itself</a>
	</strong>
	</font>
	<p>

	<a href="01a.html">
	Back to "Lustrous Performer"</a>
	<p>

	Throughout modern history, gold has played a major role in the 
	world's economies. Historically, the same general sequence of 
	events has been repeated:
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/jewels.jpg" alt="Jewelery picture jpeg" align=right>

	<li>Empires peak economically when their gold reserves peak
	<p>
	
	<li>Expansion is then continued through the artificial increase of
	wealth when gold is "watered down" by other metals
	<p>
	
	<li>Inflation sets in
	<p>
	
	<li>
	Economies and empires begin to decline and crumble
	<p>
	
	<li>
	Gold again becomes ultimate currency and cycle begins again
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
	
	<td>	
	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
