<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>One World - Spelling It Out</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	<table border=0>
	
	<tr>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
	


	<td valign=top>
	
	<h2>
	Spelling It Out (the policy) 
	</h2>
	
	<a href="03a.html">
	Back to "One World"</a>
	<p>
	
	While highly evolved, we represent just a single piece in nature's intricate puzzle. If
	one piece changes shape, the other pieces must adapt in order to fit. By understanding
	the immediate environment and our effects upon it, we can see potential problems and
	stop them before they start.
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/03spell.jpg" align=right alt="Golden Sunlight Mine, environmental tests" hspace=10 vspace=10>

	The Company operates under a detailed environmental policy which directs each mine to
	include a full account of environmental impacts and costs of any project evaluation or
	plan. Each facility is also required to have an environmental operating plan and an
	accident contingency plan.
	<p>

	In addition, a full-time senior environmental engineer works with facility management at
	each of Placer Dome's operations. Environmental engineers administer a three-tier audit
	programme which assists facilities in identifying areas for improvement. They also work
	to provide critical reviews of each facility, using both internal and external experts
	to ensure thoroughness and objectivity. All new facilities are included in the audit
	procedure guaranteeing its initial compliance is continued during and after its
	operational lifetime.
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
		
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>


	<td>	
	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
	<a href="../02expl/02a.html">
	Explorers</a> |
