<HEAD>
<TITLE>One World - Keeping it Clean</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	<table border=0>
	
	<tr>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
	

	<td valign=top>
	<h2>
	Keeping it Clean: Minimizing Enviro-Impact
	</h2>
	
	<a href="03a.html">
	Back to "One World"</a>
	<p>
	
	The best way to reduce the effects of operations on the environment is to disturb as
	little of it as possible. Sustainable development initiatives -- those that meet the
	needs of the present without compromising those of future generations -- play an
	important role in Placer Dome operations.
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/02clean.jpg" align=right alt="Campbell Mine, water treatment" hspace=10 vspace=10>
	
	The development of recent and future sites emphasizes the minimization of impact on the
	surrounding area -- placing any parts of the property having natural, social or cultural
	value off-limits.
	<p>

	Once the sites are up and running, efforts are focused on maintaining the development
	standards for the life of the facility. Ongoing monitoring activities are conducted both
	by the mine and by government to verify that the impacts on the ecosystem are as
	predicted during development.
	<p>

	As an example, sites in Canada have moved to reduce the impact of operations on nearby
	lakes and rivers. To date, over $11 million has been spent on the production and
	operation of water treatment plants for the six different mines across the country.
	<p>

	The investment has paid off as regular environmental assessments show a 93%
	reduction of contaminant discharges since 1988 with no indication of damage to the
	quality of water or food sources in those areas.
	<p>

	It is our belief that environmental management is an integral part of the operations at
	every Placer Dome mine and exploration site. 
	</td>
	<p>

	</table>
	
	<p><br>

		
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>	

	<td>	
	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	
