<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>One World - Protecting People</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	<br>

	<table border=0>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/00a.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	<br>
	

	<td valign=top>
	
	<td valign=top>
	
	<h2>
	The Human Factor: Protecting People
	</h2>
	
	<a href="03a.html">
	Back to "One World"</a>
	<p>
	
	Regardless of how big an organization becomes, its success is dependent upon the
	individuals associated with it. The health and safety of Placer Dome's employees,
	contractors and relevant publics are always priority.
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/03people.jpg" align=right alt="Zaldivar Mine Employees" hspace=10 vspace=10>



	<strong>
	Placer Dome People
	</strong>
	<p>

	All employees undergo stringent safety training, encompassing any use, maintenance and
	emergency handling of equipment and their relevant chemicals. The average lost-time
	accident frequency for Placer Dome employees has been and continues to be well below the
	industry average.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Our Friends, the Contractors
	</strong>
	<p>

	Major efforts have been taken to improve the safety performance of our contractors
	as well. As a first step, an internal task force was formed to develop comprehensive
	guidelines on safety in all dealings with contractors -- from the bidding process
	through to site enforcement. Safety reports on contractors now receive the same
	scrutiny as those for our own operations.
	<p>

	Placer Dome Technical Services and Comp&#227;nia Minera Zald&#237;var won a Chilean
	award in 1995 for safety performance during construction of the Zald&#237;var Mine.
	<p>

	To strengthen the application of our Occupational Health and Safety Policy, health
	protection programmes -- in place at all operations -- are reviewed regularly to ensure
	consistently high standards of protection at each mine.
	<p>

	<strong>
	A Large Group: The Public
	</strong>
	<p>

	As many of the areas explored and mined by Placer Dome are in developing countries, it
	is important that the Company's operations do not have a negative effect on everyday
	life.
	<p>

	For example, ground water and air quality tests are done on a regular basis to ensure
	any potential contaminants are recognized and proper action is taken.
	<p>

	In addition, the Company has taken efforts to assist those communities with which they
	do business. Local workers are used whenever possible and the development of major mining
	projects in the area helps to strengthen the local marketplace.
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	
			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>

	<td>	
	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
