<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Bald Mountain Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/baldmtn.jpg" alt="Bald Mountain Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>



	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Bald Mountain Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	The Bald Mountain open pit gold mine is located in White Pine County,
	northeastern Nevada, USA. The mine started as a 2,300 litres-per-minute
	heap leach gold project in 1983. In 1985 the plant was upgraded to a
	4,600 litres-per-minute commercial facility processing 600,000
	tonnes of ore per year with four years of reserves. The Bald
	Mountain open pit mine life at December 31, 1995 was 7.5 years and
	tonnage crushed had increased to 2,500,000 tonnes of ore per year.
	Multiple open pits and two semi-portable crushers are operated.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	110 kilometres southeast of Elko and 110 kilometres northwest of Ely, Nevada.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 114,215 ounces (1994 - 120,289) of gold which
	included production from both the Bald Mountain operation and the
	Alligator Ridge project. From the start of operations in 1983,
	735,866 ounces of gold have been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $250 per ounce (1994 -
	$214) of gold and the total cost was $352 per ounce (1994 - $302) of
	gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows: mine (40%), mill
	(31%), plant (5%) and other (23%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Bald Mountain ore is crushed in two stages and placed on leach pads.
	Heap leach solutions are processed in a 9,100 litres-per-minute
	carbon recovery plant. Low grade ore is processed without crushing.
	The Alligator Ridge project ore is crushed in three stages and
	placed on leach pads. Solution is processed at a rate of 4,200
	litres-per-minute through the carbon recovery plant.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 (including the Alligator Ridge project) contained
	964,000 ounces (1994 - 838,000) of gold in 11,373,000 tonnes of ore
	grading 2.6 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	7.5 years at December 31, 1995 (excluding the Alligator Ridge project).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization
	at December 31, 1995 (including the Alligator Ridge project)
	contained 1,273,000 ounces (1994 - 611,000) of gold in 32,058,000
	tonnes of material grading 1.2 g/t gold.

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
