<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Campbell Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/campbela.jpg" alt="Campbell mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>




	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Campbell Mine 
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Campbell mine is located at Balmertown in the Red Lake District
	of northwestern Ontario, Canada. It is in Balmer Township near the
	Manitoba-Ontario border. The property  covers an area of 756
	hectares of patented (freehold) mining lands. Production started in
	1949.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Balmertown in the Red Lake District of northwestern Ontario.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Gold production in 1995 was 323,775 ounces (1994 - 323,170). In 1995,
	526,000 tonnes of ore (1,400 tonnes per day) were milled. The head
	grade was 20.5 g/t gold and recovery was 93.8%. From the start of
	operations in 1949, 8,705,126 ounces of gold have been produced from
	13,252,308 tonnes of ore.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $137 per ounce of gold and total cost was $157
	per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows:
	mine (48%), mill (23%), plant (7%), and other (22%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 2,607,000 ounces (1994 - 2,504,000) of
	gold in 4,500,000 tonnes of ore grading 18.0 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Nine years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and
	indicated mineralization contained 482,000 ounces (699,000) of gold
	in 1,402,000 tonnes of material grading 10.7 g/t gold. The inferred
	mineralization contained 814,000 ounces (1994 - 793,000) of gold in
	1,453,000 tonnes of material grading 17.4 g/t gold.

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

