<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Cortez Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/corteza.jpg" alt="Cortez Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>



	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Cortez Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Cortez open pit gold mine commenced production in northeastern
	Nevada, USA in 1969. In 1981 the mill process was converted to a
	carbon-in-leach (CIL) plant from a standard countercurrent
	decantation Merrill-Crowe plant. In 1990 a dry grinding plant and a
	circulating fluid bed roaster were constructed for oxidation of
	refractory ores prior to processing in the CIL mill. In 1994 the
	Crescent pit, a shallow oxide portion of the South Pipeline deposit,
	was brought into production. In addition to achieving technological
	advancements in refractory ore processing, Cortez Gold Mines was the
	first Nevada gold producer to successfully employ heap leaching as a
	stand alone method of ore treatment. A new mine and mill for the Pipeline
	deposit starts production in 1997.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	60%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	100 kilometres southwest of Elko, Nevada.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 111,215 ounces (1994 - 69,608) of gold. From
	the start of operations in 1969, 1,891,783 ounces of gold have been
	produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $225 per ounce (1994 - $295) of gold and the
	total cost was $289 per ounce (1994 - $376) of gold. The 1995 cash
	cost is broken down as follows: mine (22%), mill (47%), plant (7%)
	and other (24%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	One or two stage crushing, dry grinding, circulating fluid bed
	roasting, wet grinding and CIL. Oxide ore bypasses dry grinding and
	roasting. Low grade oxide ore is heap leached. Mill throughput in
	1995 was 1,800 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 7,303,000 ounces (1994 - 4,807,000
	including the Cortez mine and Pipeline deposit) of gold in
	82,299,000 tonnes of ore grading 2.8 g/t gold.
	<br>
	The 1995 gold reserves are broken down as follows: 504,000 ounces at
	Cortez, 4,310,000 ounces at Pipeline and 2,489,000 ounces at South
	Pipeline.


	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Pipeline - 12 years (excluding South Pipeline deposit); Other Cortez
	Deposits - four years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization
	at December 31, 1995 contained 3,282,000 ounces (1994 - 6,054,00
	including the Pipeline and South Pipeline deposits) of gold in
	71,337,000 tonnes of material grading 1.4 g/t gold.
	<br>
	The 1995 gold mineralization is broken down as follows: 1,391,000
	ounces at Cortez, 330,000 ounces at Pipeline and 1,561,000 ounces at
	South Pipeline.


	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
	<a href="../01perf/01a.html">
	Performer</a> | 
	<a href="../02expl/02a.html">
	Explorers</a> |
