<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Dome Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/domemine.jpg" alt="Dome Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>


	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Dome Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Dome underground and open pit mine is located in northern
	Ontario. Underground production has been continuous since 1910 and
	open pit mining began in 1988.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%

	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Within the city limits of Timmins, Ontario. 

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 256,206 ounces. From the start of operations
	in 1910, 12,629,898 ounces of gold have been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $243 per ounce of gold and the total cost was
	$314 per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as
	follows: mine (66%), mill (17%), plant (5%), and other (13%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Gold is recovered using a combination of gravity concentration and
	cyanidation techniques. The expanded  flowsheet for the
	9,100-tonnes-per-day operation consists of primary crushing,
	secondary crushing, rod/ball mill grinding, gravity concentration,
	cyanide leaching, carbon-in-pulp (CIP) gold recovery, stripping,
	electrowinning and carbon reactivation. Mill throughput in 1995
	averaged 7,600 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995, contained 3,230,000 ounces of gold in 33,808,000
	tonnes of ore grading 3.0 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Nine years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground and open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and
	indicated mineralization contained 813,000 ounces of gold in
	11,790,000 tonnes of material grading 2.1 g/t gold. 

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
