<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Endako Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/endakoa.jpg" alt="Endako Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>




	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Endako Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Endako open pit molybdenum mine is located in central British
	Columbia, Canada and commenced production in June 1965. A plant to produce
	Ultrapure, a high grade molybdenum  disulphide additive for use in
	a wide range of special lubricants, was commissioned in 1980. The
	mine temporarily ceased production between 1982 and 1986 due to low
	market demand and prices, and was returned to full operations by
	October 1988.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	185 kilometres west of Prince George, British Columbia.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 14,410,000 pounds (1994 - 13,670,000) of
	molybdenum. From the start of operations in June 1965, 343,984,000
	pounds of molybdenum have been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Primary crusher, secondary and tertiary crushers, rod mills and ball
	mills, rougher, scavenger and cleaner flotation, regrind mills,
	dryer, roaster and Ultrapure plant. Mill throughput in 1995 was
	28,600 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 178,000,000 pounds (1994 - 200,000,000)
	of molybdenum in 104,843,000 tonnes of ore grading 0.077%
	molybdenum.
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/endakoc.jpg" alt="Endako Mine #2" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Ten years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization
	at December 31, 1995 contained 205,000,000 pounds (1994 -
	199,000,000) of molybdenum in 155,009,000 tonnes of material grading
	0.06% molybdenum.

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
