<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Golden Sunlight Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/goldsun.jpg" alt="Golden Sunlight mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>



	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Golden Sunlight Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Golden Sunlight open pit gold mine is located in southwestern
	Montana, USA and started production in 1983. Initially, three stages of
	mining were planned but ongoing exploration has added two additional
	stages and three satellite orebodies to the overall mine plan.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Near Butte, southwestern Montana.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 89,799 ounces of gold, limited by a
	temporary mill closure. From the start of operations in 1983,
	1,202,995 ounces of gold have been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost and total cost from February through
	December were $239 and $386 per ounce of gold, respectively. The
	cash and total costs for all of 1995 were $259 and $408 per ounce of
	gold, respectively. The 1995 cash cost of $259 is broken down as follows:
	mine (14%), mill (52%), plant (7%), and other (27%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	The ore treatment plant is based on conventional carbon-in-pulp (CIP)
	technology, with the addition of a Sand Tailing Retreatment (STR)
	gold recovery plant to recover gold that would otherwise be lost to
	tailing. The gold is refined into dor&#233; at the mine site. Mill
	throughput in 1995 averaged 6,200 tonnes per operating day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 1,974,000 ounces of gold in 32,451,000
	tonnes of ore grading 1.9 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	14 years at December 31, 1994, including four years of heap leaching.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and
	indicated mineralization contained 865,000 ounces of gold in
	14,409,000 tonnes of material grading 1.9 g/t gold. 

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
	<a href="../01perf/01a.html">
	Performer</a> | 
