<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Granny Smith Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/grannysa.jpg" alt="Granny Smith Mine" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Granny Smith Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Granny Smith open pit gold mine located in Western Australia, Australia started
	production in February 1990. The operation consists of three discontinuous deposits
	at the Granny Smith mine plus four satellite deposits.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	45.2%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Western Australia, 23 kilometres south of Laverton, which is approximately 950
	kilometres northeast of Perth.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 219,083 ounces of gold. From the start of operations in
	February 1990, 1,174,691 ounces of gold have been produced.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The 1995 cash cost was $257 per ounce of gold and the total
	cost was $345 per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows:
	mine (57%), mill (31%), plant (2%) and other (10%).
	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	The processing plant consists of crushing circuits for fresh and oxide ores
	followed by a semi-autogenous grinding (SAG) mill in closed circuit with a cone
	crusher, a ball mill, an agitation leaching and carbon-in-pulp (CIP) circuit and a
	gold recovery plant with carbon reactivation. Mill throughput in 1995 was 11,100
	tonnes per day.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at December 31, 1995
	contained 524,000 ounces of gold in 8,936,000 tonnes of ore grading 1.8 g/t gold.
	<p>

	<img src="../gfx/grannysb.jpg" alt="Granny Smith Mine #2" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Three years at December 31, 1995.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and indicated
	mineralization contained 653,000 ounces of gold in 10,430,000 tonnes of material
	grading 2.0 g/t gold. 
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
