<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Kidston Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/kidstona.jpg" alt="Kidston Mine" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Kidston Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Kidston open pit gold mine is located in north Queensland, Australia. Mine
	production began in 1985. Current mining is from the Wises Hill pit and, some 500
	metres to the northeast, the recently outlined Eldridge pit which will extend the
	life of the mine into the next decade. Mining of the Eldridge near surface reserve
	commenced in the North Knob area in mid 1994 and continued in 1995.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	52.8%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	North Queensland, Australia. About 280 kilometres west of Townsville and 260
	kilometres southwest of Cairns.
		<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 205,878 ounces of gold. From the start of operations in
	March 1985, 2,342,383 ounces of gold have been produced.
		<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The 1995 cash cost was $293 per ounce of gold and the total
	cost was $340 per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows;
	mine (39%), mill (47%), plant (5%) and other (9%).
		<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Gold ore processing is carried out in a semi-autogenous grinding (SAG) mill with
	recycle crushing and ball milling. This is followed by conventional cyanide
	leaching. Precious metals are recovered using carbon-in-pulp (CIP) and carbon
	column technology and subsequent carbon stripping, electrowinning and smelting.
	Mill throughput in 1995 was 16,700 tonnes per day. Mill head grade continued to
	fall as predicted by the mine plan.
	<p>

	<img src="../gfx/kidstonb.jpg" alt="Kidston Mine 2" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at December 31, 1995
	contained 1,631,000 ounces of gold in 43,794,000 tonnes of ore grading 1.2 g/t
	gold.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	6.5 years at December 31, 1995.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and indicated
	mineralization contained 831,000 ounces of gold in 39,137,000 tonnes of material
	grading 0.7 g/t gold.
		<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
	<a href="../01perf/01a.html">
	Performer</a> | 
	<a href="../02expl/02a.html">
	Explorers</a> |
	<a href="../03world/03a.html">
	One  World</a> |
