<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Kiena Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/kienab.jpg" alt="Kiena Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>



	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Kiena Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Kiena underground gold mine located in Quebec, Canada, started production
	in 1981. Development of the lower levels of the mine was approved in
	1990 following a successful exploration program in 1989 to further
	define the extension of the ore body at depth. The development
	continued in 1995 and is expected to be completed in early 1996.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Val d'Or, Quebec

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 86,621 ounces of gold (1994 - 83,044) of gold.
	From the start of operations in 1981, 1,007,199 ounces of gold have
	been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $238 per ounce (1994 - $215) of gold and the
	total cost was $326 per ounce (1994 - $307) of gold. The 1995 cash
	cost is broken down as follows: mine (51%), mill (22%), plant (9%),
	and other (18%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Gold is extracted by the carbon-in-pulp (CIP) process. Mill
	throughput in 1995 was 1,500 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 570,000 ounces (1994 - 621,000) of gold
	in 3,671,000 tonnes of ore grading 4.8 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Seven years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and
	indicated mineralization contained 254,000 ounces (1994 - 286,000)
	of gold in 1,905,000 tonnes of material grading 4.1 g/t gold. 

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
