<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - La Coipa Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/lacoipaa.jpg" alt="La Coipa Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>




	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	La Coipa Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	La Coipa open pit gold and silver mine is located in northern Chile.
	The original 1,000 tonnes-per-day processing plant operated for 20
	months before start up of the expanded 15,000 tonnes-per-day
	facility in October 1991. Mill production capacity was increased to 17,000 tonnes per day in
	1994 by modifying the grinding circuits.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	50%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Northern Chile. Approximately 140 kilometres northeast of the town
	of Copiapo and 1,000 kilometres north of Santiago.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 282,084 ounces of gold and 9,426,000 ounces
	of silver. From the start of operations in July 1989, 1,082,922
	ounces of gold and 48,485,831 ounces of silver have been produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The 1995 cash cost was $162 per equivalent
	ounce of gold and the total cost was $252 per equivalent ounce of
	gold. Silver is converted to equivalent ounces of gold at a gold to
	silver ratio of 73.5:1. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as
	follows: mine (8%), mill (62%), plant (6%) and other (25%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	The processing plant consists of a primary crushing circuit, a
	semi-autogenous grinding mill/ball mill/crusher (SABC) grinding
	circuit, a leaching circuit, a filtering/washing circuit, a
	Merrill-Crowe plant and a refinery. Mill throughput in 1995 was
	15,700 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 2,274,000 ounces (1994 - 2,644,000) of
	gold and 238,196,000 ounces (1994 - 219,308,000) of silver in
	88,436,000 tonnes of ore grading 0.8 g/t gold and 83.8 g/t silver.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Fifteen years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization
	at December 31, 1995 contained 452,000 ounces of gold and 20,752,000
	ounces of silver in 16,112,000 tonnes of material grading 0.9 g/t
	gold and 40.1 g/t silver.

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
