<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Las Cristinas Project</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/laschris.jpg" alt="Las Cristinas Project" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	<p>




	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Las Cristinas Project
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	Positive feasibility study was announced March 26, 1996 and approval
	for construction of a mine on August 1, 1996, at a cost of $536
	million. Construction began in the fourth quarter of 1996 and
	production is scheduled to commence in 1998.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	70%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Southeastern Venezuela
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Total annual production is estimated to be 450,000 ounces of gold per
	year. Placer Dome's share of total production equals 315,000 ounces
	of gold per year. Half of gold production to be contained in a
	copper concentrate, half in dor&#233; form.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	Cash cost: $205 per ounce. Total cost: $310 per ounce.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	Eight million ounces of gold in main Cuatro Muertos and Conductora
	zones. Placer Dome's share equals 5.6 million ounces of gold.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	At least 16 years at a mining rate of 55,000 tonnes-per-day.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Milling Rate
	</strong><br>
	40,000 tonnes per day. The processing circuit has been optimized 
	to reduce costs and to make water and tailing management cleaner
	and safer.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization at December
	31, 1995 contained 9.2 million ounces of gold in 224 metric tonnes of material
	grading 1.3 g/t gold. 
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
