<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Misima Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/misima.jpg" alt="Misima mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>


	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Misima Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Misima open pit gold and silver mine is located on Misima Island in Papua New
	Guinea (PNG). Open pit mining began in 1989 on a five-stage mining plan.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	60.3%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Eastern Misima Island, PNG.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 331,232 ounces of gold and 1,092,128 ounces of silver. From
	the start of operations in 1989, 2,170,395 ounces of gold and 12,975,071 ounces of
	silver have been produced.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The 1995 cash cost was $147 per ounce of gold and the total
	cost was $213 per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows;
	mine (43%), mill (43%), plant (7%) and other (6%).
	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Run of mine material goes directly into the grinding circuit. The grinding product
	is leached and the dissolved metal is recovered in a conventional carbon-in-pulp
	(CIP) process. The metal stripped from the carbon is precipitated with zinc and
	subsequently refined to dor&#233;. Mill throughput in 1995 was 15,700 tonnes
	per day.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at December 31, 1995
	contained 1,272,000 ounces of gold and 11,270,000 ounces of silver in 36,063,000
	tonnes of ore grading 1.1 g/t gold and 9.7 g/t silver.	
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Six years at December 31, 1995.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995, the measured and indicated
	mineralization contained 610,000 ounces of gold and 4,401,000 ounces of silver
	in 20,628,000 tonnes of material grading 0.9 g/t gold and 6.6 g/t silver.
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
	<font size=-1>
