<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Mt. Rawdon Project</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	
	<img src="../gfx/mtrawdon.jpg" alt="Mt. Rawdon" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Mt. Rawdon Project
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	Feasibility study for heap leach project due for completion in 1996
	with an investment decision to be considered shortly thereafter. A
	positive investment decision will lead to a nine-month contruction
	phase and mine start-up in 1997.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	52.8%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	270 kilometres north-west of Brisbane, Australia
	<p>

	<strong>
	Annual Production
	</strong><br>
	Placer Dome's share of production is estimated at 50,000 ounces per year.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	Cash cost: $260 per ounce. 
	<p>

	<strong>
	Capital Costs
	</strong><br>
	$25 million
	<p>

	<strong>
	Feasibility Completion
	</strong><br>
	Third quarter, 1996
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization at December
	31, 1995 contained 1.0 million ounces of gold in 26.7 tonnes of material
	grading 1.2 g/t. Placer Dome's share equals 520,000 ounces.
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
