<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Musselwhite Project</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Musselwhite Project
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	<img src="../gfx/mussel.jpg" alt="Musselwhite Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=10>
	A decision was made in February 1996 to construct a gold mine at the
	Musselwhite property in northwestern Ontario, Canada, at a capital cost of
	$190 million. Development of a mine and construction of processing
	facilities started immediately in order to commence production in
	the second quarter of 1997.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	68.1%

	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Northwestern Ontario, Canada. About 500 kilometres north of Thunder Bay. 
	
	<p>

	<strong>
	Estimated Capital Costs
	</strong><br>
	The construction cost estimate is approximately $190 million.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Estimated Production
	</strong><br>
	Total production is estimated to be 2,107,000 ounces of gold over a
	10.6-year mine life.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Estimated Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The average cash cost over the life of the
	mine is estimated to be approximately $200 per ounce of gold and
	average total cost is estimated to be approximately $310 per ounce.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Proposed Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Gravity concentration using a Knelson concentrator and shaking tables
	followed by leaching and CIP is the optimum gold extraction method
	for the Musselwhite ore. Mill throughput is estimated at 3,300
	tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves contain
	1,762,000 ounces of gold in 9,755,000 tonnes of ore grading 5.6 g/t
	gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	10.6 years
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground and open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization
	contained 617,000 ounces of gold in 3,290,000 tonnes of material
	grading 5.8 g/t gold. 
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
