<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Mulatos Project</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>

	<img src="../gfx/mulatos.jpg" alt="Mulatos Mine" align=right vspace=5 hspace=10>
	<p>

	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Mulatos Project
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	Feasibility study is progressing for completion by the end of 1996. An
	investment decision will be made in early 1997 on construction of the 
	heap leaching project. A positive investment decision will lead to 
	construction start-up in early 1997 and mine start-up in 1998.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	70%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Sierra Madre, Sonora, Mexico
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Placer Dome's share of annual production is estimated to be 100,000
	ounces of gold per year.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Capital Costs
	</strong><br>
	$100 million
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization at December
	31, 1995 contained 3.4 million ounces of gold in 98.6 tonnes of material
	grading 1.1 g/t. Placer Dome's share equals 2.352 million ounces.
