<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Porgera Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	

	<img src="../gfx/porgera.jpg" alt="Porgera Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>

	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Porgera Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Porgera underground and open pit gold mine is located in the highlands of
	Papua New Guinea (PNG). Underground mining started in September 1990.
	Pre-production open pit stripping began in August 1991 and the open pit commenced
	production in March 1993.
	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	18.8%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	250 kilometres west of Mount Hagen in the Enga Province of PNG.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 848,872 ounces of gold. From the start of operations in
	September, 1990, 6,005,115 ounces of gold have been produced.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	(including royalties): The 1995 cash cost was $197 per ounce of gold and the total
	cost was $267 per ounce of gold. The 1995 cash cost is broken down as follows;
	mine (52%), mill (21%), plant (6%) and other (21%).
	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Ore is ground and then floated for sulphide extraction. The concentrate is then
	subjected to an oxidation process and a conventional carbon-in-pulp (CIP) cyanide
	leach. Mill throughput in 1995 was 8,300 tonnes per day.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at December 31, 1995
	contained 8,894,000 of gold in 63,708,000 tonnes of ore grading 4.3 g/t gold.
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/porgerab.jpg" alt="Porgera Mine #2" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Twelve years at December 31, 1995.
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground and open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	The measured and indicated mineralization at December
	31, 1995 contained 1,910,000 ounces of gold in 20,200,000 tonnes of material
	grading 3.0 g/t gold. 
	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
	<center>
