<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sites - Sigma Mine</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">
	
	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>

	<table border=0>
	<tr>

	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/04butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a></td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<img src="../gfx/08head.gif" alt="The Sites header gif">
	<p>
	
	
	<a href="08a.html">
	Back to Sites Map</a>
	<p>
	
	<img src="../gfx/sigma.jpg" alt="Sigma Mine" align=right vspace=10 hspace=5>
	<p>


	<font size=+2>
	<strong>
	Sigma Mine
	</strong>
	</font>
	<br>
	
	The Sigma underground and open pit gold mine is located in
	northwestern Quebec, Canada. The underground mine (Sigma I) has operated
	continuously since production started in 1937. The open pit mine
	(Sigma II), located approximately 24 kilometres from the underground
	mine, started production in 1984.

	<p>
	
	<strong>
	Ownership Interest
	</strong><br>
	100%
	<p>

	<strong>
	Location
	</strong><br>
	Bourlamaque Township, Abitibi County, northwestern Quebec. About two
	kilometres east of the Val d'Or business district.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production
	</strong><br>
	Production in 1995 was 78,262 ounces (1994 - 85,145) of gold. From
	the start of operations in 1937, 4,189,659 ounces of gold have been
	produced.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Production Costs
	</strong><br>
	The 1995 cash cost was $367 per ounce (1994 - $298) of gold and the
	total cost was $384 per ounce (1994 - $310) of gold. The 1995 cash
	cost is broken down as follows: mine (74%), mill (13%), plant (5%)
	and other (9%).

	<p>

	<strong>
	Processing Plant
	</strong><br>
	Conventional ball milling followed by cyanidation and zinc
	precipitation. Mill throughput in 1995 was 1,660 tonnes per day.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Ore Reserves
	</strong><br>
	The proven and probable ore reserves at
	December 31, 1995 contained 448,000 ounces (1994 - 499,000) of gold
	in 3,578,000 tonnes of ore grading 3.9 g/t gold.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mine Life 
	</strong><br>
	Five years at December 31, 1995.

	<p>

	<strong>
	Mining Method
	</strong><br>
	Underground and open pit
	<p>

	<strong>
	Mineralization
	</strong><br>
	At December 31, 1995 the measured and
	indicated  mineralization contained 141,000 ounces (1994 - 112,000)
	of gold in 838,000 tonnes of material grading 5.2 g/t gold. 

	<p></td>
	
	</table>
	<p>

			
	<a name="00">
	<table border=0></a>
	<tr>

	<td width=120></td>
		
	<td>	

	<img src="../gfx/menuba1.gif" alt="Placer Dome footer gif">
	<br>
