	<h2>
	Career Opportunities with Placer Dome
	</h2>
	
	<a href="#01">
	<strong>Chief Geologist</strong></a><br>
	
	<hr><p>
	
	
    <a name="01">
	<strong>Chief Geologist</a></strong><p>
    
    <font size=-1>
	This is an excellent opportunity for a proven leader to manage and 
	direct a department of 12 geologists and technicians. You will 
	control, plan and provide direction, to guide mining, development and 
	exploration within the mine and immediate surroundig area. You will 
	also participate in the evaluation, acquisition and exploration of 
	properties in the Red Lake Belt.
	
	<p>
	Along with a BSc in geology or geological engineering, you have at 
	least 10 years' related experience, ideally with gold minng 
	operations. Experience with computerized geographical modelling is a 
	must and you should have advanced knowledge of geostatistical and 
	reserve estimation techniques. Strong supervisory  skills and 
	excellent written and verbal communications abilities are essential 
	for success in this key role.
	<p>
	Campbell Mine, a division of Placer Dome Canada, is an underground 
	gold mine operation located in Balmerton, part of the Red Lake 
	district of Ontario. In operation since 1949, with approximately 400 
	non-unionized employees, it is one of the highest grade, lowest cost 
	gold mines in the world.
	<p>
	Should you like to take advantage of this opportunity, please submit 
	your resume <strong>as soon as possible to:<br>
	
	Brian Larson, Human Resources<br> 
	Superintendent<br> 
	Placer Dome Canada Limited<br> 
	Campbell Mine<br>
	P.O. Box 10<br>
	Balmerton, Ontario<br> 
	P0V 1C0<br>
	Fax: (807)735-2765
    </font>
	</strong>
	</td>
	</table>
