    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome achieves 91% ownership of Highlands Gold</h2>
	
    <strong>February 7, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc., in its A$0.75 per share bid for
     Highlands Gold Limited, has taken its holding in Highlands to more
     than 91%.  This includes a small proportion of legally binding
     undertakings to tender to the offer.  Once the undertakings are
     converted to formal acceptances, Placer Dome will be entitled to move
     to compulsory acquisition.
<p>
            Placer Dome has agreed to extend its offer to allow
     shareholders with small holdings to accept the offer.  The extension
     will also allow people who have purchased Highlands shares this week
     to accept the offer.
<p>
            "Placer Dome is extremely pleased with the outcome of the
     offer," John Willson, President and Chief Executive Officer, said.
     Highlands Gold owns 25% of the Porgera Mine in Papua New Guinea.  The
     offer is now scheduled to close on Saturday, February 15, 1997.


    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
