    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Agreement signed for Las Cristinas Mine</h2>
	
    <strong>February 6, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces that Placer Dome Latin
     America and Corporacion Venezolana de Guayana (CVG) signed the
     definitive shareholders' agreement and reached accord on terms for
     construction of the mine and power line required to develop the Las
     Cristinas project in Venezuela.
<p>
            Elias Ynaty, President of CVG and William M. Hayes, President
     of Placer Dome Latin America, signed the shareholders' agreement in
     Caracas today and expressed confidence in the success of the project,
     estimated to cost US$576 million.
<p>
            Mr. Ynaty said: "I reiterate my faith that this will be one of
     the most important mines in the world.  We have begun the process to
     obtain the exoneration of the wholesale tax, as well as to obtain the
     rest of the permits from government agencies, in order to initiate the
     construction of this important project."
<p>
            Mr. Hayes said the signing of the agreement, and accord on the
     power line and mine construction contracts, will facilitate obtaining
     financing for the project for the joint venture company, Minera Las
     Cristinas, C.A. (Minca) (PDG 70% interest).
<p>
            In terms of the date to initiate construction, Mr. Hayes said
     that this will hinge on the granting of the environmental permits and
     especially the wholesale tax exoneration.  On the latter he expressed
     optimism, saying, "We trust that the Economic Cabinet of the
     Venezuelan Government will recognize the importance that the
     exoneration will have for the development of the mining sector during
     the pre-operations phase, which will allow us to rehire Minca
     personnel as well as to generate approximately 2,500 direct jobs
     during the construction of the mine."


    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
