	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome restructures Detour Lake Mine</h2>
	
    <strong>February 4, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces it is taking steps to
     return its Detour Lake Mine in Canada to profitability.  As part of a
     restructuring programme, 103 of 347 active employees are being laid
     off effective February 12, 1997.
<p>
        Cash production costs averaged US$401/oz. in 1996, primarily due to
     a change in continuity of the main ore zone which reduced underground
     production rates.  In addition to returning the mine to profitability,
     reduced production costs are also expected to increase the viability
     of the prospective QK Zone of mineralization, currently being
     explored.  An accelerated exploration programme on the QK Zone is due
     to be completed by mid-1997.
<p>
        Detour Lake's forecast gold production in 1997 is expected to be
     reduced to 117,000 ozs. from 147,000 ozs., with negligible impact on
     Placer Dome's target of 2.3 million ozs. for the year.

    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
