	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome welcomes favourable report on Placer Pacific</h2>
	
    <strong>February 4, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> -  Placer Dome Inc. today welcomed a favourable
     independent expert's conclusion and an intended recommendation by the
     independent Directors, released by Placer Pacific Limited.  Placer
     Dome has launched a takeover bid for the 24.6% publicly owned shares
     of Placer Pacific.
<p>
            The independent expert's report, compiled by Grant Samuel &
     Associates, found Placer Dome's offer of one Placer Dome share for 15
     Placer Pacific shares to be "fair and reasonable" and that "the
     Directors of Placer Pacific would be justified in recommending to
     shareholders that they accept the offer."
<p>
            "We are pleased with the independent expert's conclusion and
     the intended recommendation from the independent Directors," John
     Willson, Placer Dome's President and Chief Executive Officer, said.
     "This report confirms the fairness of our offer to Placer Pacific
     shareholders.  We look forward to the Placer Pacific Board meeting to
     finalize their response."
<p>
            Placer Dome dispatched its offer documents on January 24, 1997.
      The offer is scheduled to close on February 25, 1997. However, Placer
     Pacific has requested that Placer Dome extend its offer to accommodate
     printing and dispatch of Placer Pacific's response document.  Placer
     Dome is considering a short extension of the offer.





    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
