    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome moves to more than 76.5% ownership of Highlands Gold</h2>
	
    <strong>February 3, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc., in its A$0.75 per share bid for
     Highlands Gold Limited of Papua New Guinea, has taken its holding in
     Highlands Gold to more than 76.5 per cent.
<p>
        "We are extremely pleased with the success of our offer and have
     received phone calls from many more shareholders who intend to
     accept," John Willson, President and Chief Executive Officer, said.
     "We are expecting to receive acceptances from those shareholders
     before our offer closes at the end of the week."
<p>
        Placer Dome's offer is scheduled to close on Saturday, February 8,
     1997.



    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
