    <p>

	
    <h2>Highlands Gold appoints Placer Dome representatives to Board</h2>
	
    <strong>January 28, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Highlands Gold Limited has announced the
     appointment of three Placer Dome Inc. representatives to its
     five-member Board of Directors.
    <p>
     Dick Zandee, Managing Director of Placer Pacific Limited, has
     been appointed Chairman, Russell Barwick, Managing Director of Placer
     Niugini Limited, is Managing Director, and Mel Togolo, General Manager
     Corporate Affairs with Placer Niugini, is a Director.
<p>
            Mr. Zandee said he is keen to ensure a smooth transition of
     Highlands to Placer management.  Mr. Barwick said the new Directors
     will be cooperating with the independent Directors of Highlands in
     relation to their proposed spin-off of Highlands Pacific Limited.
<p>
            Placer Dome's A$0.75 per share bid for all of the shares of
     Highlands Gold is scheduled to close on February 8, 1997.



    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       

        
