<HEAD>
<TITLE>Placer Dome - The Latest</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	
	<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/06butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a>
	</td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<table border=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top colspan=2>
	<img src="../gfx/09head.gif" alt="The Latest header gif">
	</td>
	
	
	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome's offer for Highlands to close on Saturday</h2>
	
    <strong>January 14, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Highlands Gold Limited 
     shareholders have three days left to accept Placer Dome Inc's 
     A$0.75-a-share takeover offer. The offer is scheduled to close on 
     Saturday 18 January.
    <p>
        "Obviously many Highlands shareholders like our 75 
        cents-a-share offer," Placer Dome Inc. President and Chief 
        Executive Officer Mr. John Willson said.  "We are encouraged 
        by the strong level of acceptances we have received, both from 
        small shareholders and institutions.
<p>
        "While the Highlands' board has stopped short of recommending 
        Placer Dome's offer to its shareholders, it has warned 
        shareholders that Highlands' shares could trade below the 
        offer price when the bid closes.
<p>
        "The Highlands' board has also advised shareholders with small 
        unmarketable parcels that they may find the cash offer 
        attractive," he said.
<p>
        Mr. Willson also said Placer Dome could not understand why 
        Highlands is pursuing a restructuring that the market has 
        rejected.
<p>
        "The failed underwriting was trying to float Highlands' 
        non-gold assets at about A$200 million.  On the basis of our 
        now withdrawn offer to buy the Porgera assets for A$316 
        million, Placer Dome's A$0.75-a-share offer values these same 
        assets at A$143 million.
<p>
        "Looking at market values rather than theoretical valuations 
        contained in the independent expert's report, Placer Dome 
        believes its offer for Highlands Gold shares is demonstrably 
        fair and reasonable,"
     Mr. Willson said.

    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       
    
    <p>
	
    
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
    <tr>
	<td colspan=2 align=center>
			
	<a name="00">

