    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome proposes merger with Bre-X Minerals</h2>
	
    <strong>January 14, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces 
     it has presented a proposal to Bre-X Minerals Ltd. for Placer 
     Dome to merge with Bre-X, and for Placer Dome to take the lead in 
     developing the Busang gold property in Kalimantan.
    <p>
        "We understand Indonesia's interest in the development of 
        Busang and believe that a combination of Bre-X and Placer Dome 
        will best serve that interest," said John Willson, President 
        and Chief Executive Officer.  "We are experienced in building 
        mines like Busang and have the financial strength to fund 
        construction."
    <p>
        He added: "Our proposal provides for significant Indonesian 
        ownership of this world-class deposit, as well as an 
        opportunity for Bre-X shareholders to obtain attractive value, 
        plus continuing participation in Busang.  It also provides 
        further growth for Placer Dome."
    <p>
        The proposal is contained in the attached letter from John 
        Willson to David Walsh, President and Chief Executive Officer 
        of Bre-X Minerals.  The proposal provides:
    <p>
     <li>Indonesian participation of up to a 40% equity interest in the 
     project; 
     <li>A stock-for-stock "merger of equals" between Bre-X and 
     Placer Dome; 
     <li>Staged construction of a mine and plant of up to 
     200,000 tonnes per day costing up to US$1.7 billion, to start 
     gold production in 1999. Depending on the ultimate optimum scale, 
     production would average 3 to 4 million ounces per year.
    <p>
     Placer Dome's proposal would be subject to negotiation with 
     Bre-X and the Indonesian Government, customary due diligence 
     procedures, issuance of a suitable Contract of Work, 
     satisfactory resolution of ownership issues, and regulatory 
     and shareholder approvals.

    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       
    
    <p>
	
    
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
