    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome disappointed as underwriting fails -
        offer for Highlands declared final</h2>
	
    <strong>January 10, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>


     Vancouver, Canada - Placer Dome Inc. has been advised by Highlands
     Gold Limited that the proposed underwriting of Highlands Pacific
     Limited has not been concluded.  The proposed underwriting was
     designed to support a A$160 million raising of capital at A$0.30 per
     share, necessary to enable Highlands Gold's proposed restructuring.
    <p>
        Placer Dome had offered to buy Porgera for A$316.1 million (US$250
     million), or A$0.56 per Highlands share, provided that a A$160 million
     underwriting was secured for the non-Porgera assets.  Placer Dome's
     conditional offer to buy Porgera has now been withdrawn.
    <p>
        "We are disappointed that this underwriting failed, but we remain
     committed to our A$0.75 a share offer for Highlands," Placer Dome
     President and Chief Executive Officer, Mr. John Willson said.
    <p>
        "Placer Dome's offer price for Highlands for A$0.75 is final.
     There will be no increase," Mr. Willson declared.
    <p>
       The cash offer is scheduled to remain open until January 18, 1997.

    <p>
    For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
       
    
    <p>
	
    
    <br><br>
    </td>
