<HEAD>
<TITLE>Placer Dome - The Latest</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	
	<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/06butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a>
	</td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<table border=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top colspan=2>
	<img src="../gfx/09head.gif" alt="The Latest header gif">
	</td>
	
	
	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome indicates agreement in principle to Highlands Gold proposal, 
        providing underwriting is secured</h2>
	
    <strong>January 6, 1997</strong>
    
    <p>


	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. said today it is prepared to 
     enter into an agreement with Highlands Gold Limited, a Papua New 
     Guinea company, to acquire Highlands' 25% interest in the Porgera 
     Mine, subject to conditions.
    <p>
        The proposal by Highlands Gold would enable Placer Dome to acquire the 25% 
        stake and related assets for A$316 million (US$250 million) effective 
        December 31, 1996.  The price is equivalent to the high point of a valuation 
        prepared by Baring Brothers Burrows & Co., an independent expert in 
        Australia, for those assets.  The purchase price would be adjusted for any 
        other assets, costs or liabilities being assumed by Placer Dome. <p> 
        Placer Dome is prepared to enter into an implementation agreement provided 
        that:<br> 
        <li>Highlands Gold concludes an acceptable underwriting agreement by Friday, 
        January 10, 1997 to raise at least A$160 million (US$126 million) for the new 
        company required to be formed under its proposal. 
        <li>This new entity, Highlands Pacific Limited, would own the Ramu and 
        Frieda-Nena projects in Papua New Guinea and other Highlands' exploration 
        assets. 
        <li>All necessary approvals and tax rulings are received from the Government 
        of Papua New Guinea.
        <p>
        Meanwhile, Placer Dome's A$0.75 per share cash offer for all of the      
        shares of Highlands Gold is scheduled to close on January 18, 1997.  Placer 
        Dome subsidiaries currently own more than 46% of Highlands Gold.
        <p>
        Highlands Gold's announcement on this matter is attached for 
        information.
       <p>
       For further information:<br>
        Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	    Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>
        <p>
		<hr width=40% align=center>
		<p>
		<h3>From the offices of Highlands Gold Limited</h3>
		
		<p>
		
		The Directors of Highlands Gold announced today that they have 
		received Placer Dome's agreement in principle to Highlands' 
		restructuring proposal, subject to a satisfactory underwriting for 
		A$160 million.
		<p>
		Under Highlands' proposal, all of Highlands Gold's assets other than 
		its 25% interest in Porgera (and the receivable from Orogen Minerals) 
		are to be transferred to a new company, Highlands Pacific Limited, in 
		return for the issue to Highlands Gold of 564.5 million shares (the 
		same number of shares in Highlands Gold).
		<p>
		By way of scheme of management, all of the shares in Highlands Gold 
		held by shareholders other than Placer in completion of Placer's 
		takeover offer will be cancelled. In exchange, those shareholders will 
		recive a capital return, planned to be A$0.65 cents cash per share, and 
		one share in Highlands Pacific, for each share held in Highlands Gold.
		<p>
		Following this cancellation, Placer will own all to the remaining 
		share capital of Highlands Gold and, therefore, will acquire full 
		ownership of Highlands' 25% interest in Porgera.
		<p>
		Placer has agreed to an acquisition price for Highlands' 25% interest 
		in Porgera (and Orogen receivable) of A$316.1 million subject to 
		settlement adjustments (including related borrowing which Placer would 
		assume) in Highlands Gold.
		<p>
		It is proposed that the shareholding entitlement in Highlands Pacific 
		otherwise attributable to Placer will be placed, and that Highlands 
		Pacific will also raise new capital to secure funding for the final 
		feasibility study on Ramu, further work on Frieda-Nena and the ongoing 
		exploration programme.
		<p>
		It is planned that the total equity raising will be at least A$160 
		million at an issue price of A$0.30 per share. It is intended to 
		provide priority to Highlands Gold shareholders in the capital 
		raising.
		<p>
		The underwriting arrangements proposed are subject to completion by 
		Friday, January 10, 1997.
		<p>
		Placer will pay to Highlands Gold sufficient funds to meet the A$0.65 
		capital return to shareholders who have not accepted the Placer offer. 
		This amount, together with funds already expended by Placer on 
		Highlands shares previously acquired and as acceptances to its 
		takeover offer, will be offset by the placement of its attributable 
		shareholding in Highlands Pacific, to reduce its net cost to A$316.1 
		million.
		<p>
		"We are pleased that Placer has accepted our offer," Highlands 
		Managing Director Mr Ian Goddard said.
		<p>
		"There has been strong institutional interest in our proposal, which 
		unlocks the value of Ramu, Frieda-Nena and Highlands' extensive 
		exploration interests. We are looking forward to finalising the 
		underwriting by the end of the week," he went on to say.
		<p>
		The scheme of arrangement under Section 192 of the PNG Companies Act 
		would be subject to approval by Highlands Gold shareholders and PNG 
		regulatory authorities. It is planned that the scheme would become 
		effective once it is approved by the National Court of Papua New 
		Guinea in late February.
		<p>
		
		Media enquiries:<p>
		
		Highlands Gold<br>
		Ian Goddard - Managing Director<br>
		(07) 3864 0720<br> 
		015 115 845<p>
		
		
		Rothschild Australia<br> 
		Ronnie Beevor - Director<br> 
		(02) 9323 2036<br>
		0414 326 184<br>

    
    <p>
	
    
    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
