    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome ownership of Highlands Gold breaks through 40%</h2>
	
    <strong>December 30, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> -  Placer Dome Inc. has received acceptances taking
     its shareholding in Highlands Gold Limited to 40.8%.  The A$0.75 a
     share takeover offer for Highlands Gold will close on Saturday,
     January 18, 1997.
	<p>
        "We are pleased that Highlands Gold shareholders have seen the
     value in our offer and have rushed to accept," Placer Dome President
     and Chief Executive Officer, Mr. John Willson said.
	<p>
        "This highly encouraging response, coupled with the fact that we
     picked up 33.3% of the company in a matter of hours when we first
     launched our offer on market, sends a clear message that our offer is
     attractive.
<p>
        "We hope that Highlands shareholders will continue to see our offer
     as attractive, particularly in the light of our reduced five business
     day cash settlement period."
    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	
    
