     A$1.37<br>
     </font>
     </td>
     </table>
     <p>
     The resulting value per share to Highlands shareholders is in fact
     higher than the current Barings' valuation range.  I believe that the
     Highlands Board and its independent expert must, therefore, conclude
     that this offer is fair and reasonable.
    <p>
     This offer is made subject to our reaching mutually agreeable detailed
     terms and entering a formal legal agreement.  Placer Dome would need
     to ensure that the transaction structure adopted would not lead to any
     onerous transaction costs and would not trigger pre-emptive rights
     under the Porgera Joint Venture agreement.  These issues, however,
     while of fundamental importance to Placer Dome, are matters of
     implementation and structure.
    <p>
     More urgently, we need to establish whether this proposal is of
     interest in-principle to the board of Highlands.  If this is the case,
     and the Highlands Board wishes to proceed with this transaction, we
     could take steps to withdraw or close our offer and proceed along the
     new path.  I would therefore ask for your reply to this letter by
     Monday, January 6, 1997.
    <p>
     I am advised that Placer Dome, having release an intentions statement
     in regard to Highlands, has an obligation to keep the market informed
     of any changes in its intentions.  I will therefore be releasing this
     letter to the market today.
    <p>
     I look forward to hearing from you.
    <p>
     Yours sincerely,
    <p>
     Placer Dome Inc.<br>
     J.M. Willson<br>
     President and Chief Executive Officer <br>


       

    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
