    <h2>Placer Dome to purchase shares of Etruscan Enterprises Ltd.</h2>
	
    <strong>December 19, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Pursuant to applicable securities requirements,
     Placer Dome Inc. today announced that it has entered into an agreement
     to purchase 4,175,275 common shares of Etruscan Enterprises Ltd. of
     Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, from Echo Bay Mines of Denver, Colorado.  Upon
     completion of the purchase, Placer Dome will hold approximately 24.3%
     of the outstanding shares of Etruscan.  The shares are being purchased
     by way of a private transaction and are being acquired by Placer Dome
     for investment purposes.
    <p>
        As announced by Etruscan on December 11, 1996, Placer Dome has
     entered into a memorandum of agreement with Etruscan concerning the
     exploration and possible development of the Samira gold deposit on the
     Tiawa property in Niger, West Africa.
    <p>
    For further information:<br>                                 
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>           
    Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>             

    <br><br>
    </td>
    </tr>
	
