    <h2>Placer Dome completes securities offering</h2>
	
    <strong>December 17, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


    <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Further to the news release of December 5, 
    1996, Placer Dome Inc. announces it has completed the sale of US$300 million of 
    junior subordinated securities to two United States underwriter syndicates for 
    distribution in U.S. capital markets.  The Corporation has issued US$200 million 
    of 8.625% securities due in the year 2045, and US$100 million of 8.500% 
    securities due in 2045, priced to yield 8.585%.  The securities are redeemable at 
    par after five and 10 years, respectively.
    <p>
     A description of the terms of the securities are set forth in a
     prospectus filed with the British Columbia Securities Commission and a
     Registration Statement filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange
     Commission.  Net proceeds from the sale of the securities will be used
     for general corporate purposes, including funding acquisitions and
     future capital expenditures.
    <p>
        Placer Dome Inc. is an international mining company and one of the
     world's largest producers of gold.

 
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
