    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome welcomes Highlands Gold Limited announcement that it will not pursue legal action</h2>
	
    <strong>December 17, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. welcomes an
	announcement from Highlands Gold Limited that Highlands will not
	proceed with any legal action against the A$0.75 a share takeover
	offer dispatched by Placer Dome today.
	<p>
	Placer Dome released additional information to the market earlier
	today following discussions with Highlands (see additional
	information below).
	<p>
	"Although not required by law, Placer Dome was happy to release this
	extra information to shareholders," Placer Dome president and Chief
	Executive Officer, Mr. John Willson said.
	<p>
	"While the offer has only been in the hands of Highlands shareholders
	for one day, Placer Dome is already processing acceptances from both
	institutional and retail investors."
	<p>
	"We are extremely pleased that Highlands shareholders now have the
	opportunity to consider and accept our offer."
	<p>
	Conditions on the offer have been removed for all but Papua New
	Guinea residents and shareholders on the Papua New Guinea register
	who await Papua New Guinea Central Bank approval. Furthermore, the
	case settlement period has been reduced to five business days from
	30 days.

    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<p>
	
	Additional information relating to the offer for Highlands Gold Ltd
	by Placer Dome Holdings Pte Ltd.
	<p>
	Highlands Gold Ltd has requested that Placer Dome Holdings Pte Ltd
	(Placer Dome Holdings) release additional information relating to
	its offer for all of the shares of Highlands Gold Ltd (Highlands).
	Although Placer Dome Holdings does not believe that this
	information is required under either Papua New Guinea law or
	Australian law, it has agreed without prejudice to make additional
	disclosures.
	<p>
	This additional information follows. It will also be dispatched to
	the shareholders of Highlands.


	<h3>Principal activities</h3>
	The offer for Highlands will be made by Placer Dome Holdings. Placer
	Dome Holdings is a company incorporated in Singapore. The principal
	activity of Placer Dome Holdings is to acquire and hold Highlands
	Gold shares.
	<p>
	Placer Dome Holdings is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Placer Dome Inc.
	(Placer Dome), a Canadian public company which is listed on the
	Toronto, Montreal, New York, Paris,  Basle, Geneva, Zurich, and
	Australian Stock Exchanges.
	<p>
	Placer Dome and its subsidiary companies, joint ventures and
	associated companies are principally engaged in the exploration
	for, and the acquisition, development and operation of, mineral
	properties. Placer Dome's principal product and source of earnings
	is gold, and significant quantities of silver, copper and molybdenum
	are also produced. At present, major mining operations are located
	in Canada, the United States, Australia, Papua New Guinea and Chile.
	Exploration work is being carried out in the abovementioned
	countries and many others elsewhere throughout the world.
	<p>
	Placer Dome was formed in 1987 under the Canada Business Corporations
	Act by the amalgamation of Placer Development Limited, Dome Mines
	Limited, and Campbell Red Lake Mines Limited. Placer Dome
	substantially continues the business previously carried on
	separately by the aforementioned companies.
	<p>
	The operations of Placer Dome are conducted through decentralized
	regional business units consisting of its wholly-owned subsidiaries
	Placer Dome Canada Limited, Placer Dome US Inc., Placer Dome Latin
	America Limited and 75.4%-owned Placer Pacific Limited, an
	Australian public company. The table below shows, as at November 30,
	1996, the principal operating assets of Placer Dome Inc. and its
	percentage ownership interest in each.
	
	<p>
