    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome warns of potential bid withdrawal</h2>
	
    <strong>December 16, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. has announced that it will take
     action to withdraw its A$0.75 a share takeover offer for Highlands
     Gold Limited if Highlands proceeds with litigation against the offer.
    <p>
     Placer Dome has completely rejected the unfounded allegations made by
     Highlands Gold in relation to the conduct of the offer.  We cannot
     condone the frustration tactics of Highlands.
    <p>
     As yet, threatened litigation has not been initiated and the offer is
     open for acceptance.  Placer Dome has dropped the offer conditions,
     for all shareholders excluding Papua New Guinea residents and
     shareholder on the Papua New Guinea register, to ensure that Highlands
     shareholders can accept the offer with certainty if they wish to do
     so.
    <p>
     The cash settlement period has been reduced to five business days from
     30 days.
    <p>
     "The offer is open now but, due to the threat of legal action I can
     offer no guarantees as to how long the offer will remain open," Placer
     Dome President and Chief Executive Officer, Mr. John Willson said.
    <p>
     "We have complied with each and every legal obligation in relation to
     the conduct of this offer.  All information we are required to
     disclose has been disclosed and we value our solid corporate
     reputation highly, as do our shareholders."

    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
