    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome rejects nondisclosure allegations made by Highlands
     Gold</h2>
	
    <strong>December 15, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. has rejected allegations made by
     Highlands Gold Limited in relation to Placer Dome's intended A$0.75 a
     share takeover offer.
    <p>
     "We are extremely disappointed that the Highlands Gold board has
     raised these completely unfounded allegations," Placer Dome President
     and Chief Executive Officer Mr. John Willson said.
    <p>
     "Placer Dome has complied with each and every legal obligation in
     relation to the conduct of this offer.  All information we are
     required to disclose has been disclosed.  We value our solid corporate
     reputation highly, as do our shareholders."
    <p>
     "We sincerely hope that any potential litigation will not jeopardize
     the ability of Highlands shareholders to receive and accept our
     offer," he said.
    <p>
     Mr. Willson said Placer Dome was still considering its response to the
     letter received by Highlands Gold, but would supply a response on
     Monday.
    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

