<TITLE>Placer Dome - The Latest</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" link="52001f" vlink="858585">

	<a href=#00>
	<img src="../gfx/pdlogosm.gif" alt="Placer Dome banner gif" border=0></a>
	
	<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top>
	<a href="../gfx/00butbar.map">
	<img src="../gfx/06butbar.gif" alt="Button links - image mapped gif" border=0 align=left ismap></a>
	</td>
	
	<td valign=top>
	<table border=0>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top colspan=2>
	<img src="../gfx/09head.gif" alt="The Latest header gif">
	</td>
	
	
	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome implements financing plan</h2>
	
    <strong>December 5, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>


     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. today announced plans to raise
     funds through the sale of assets and the issue of preferred
     securities.  As a result of both the decision to dispose of  assets,
     and the re-evaluation of two properties, Placer Dome will record a
     US$78 million after-tax charge against earnings in the fourth quarter
     in order to reflect expected recoveries.
	<p>
     "The steps we are taking are intended to sharpen our focus on core
     gold assets," said John Willson, President and Chief Executive
     Officer. "We want to realize greater value from our assets, and we
     feel we can do this by concentrating on higher-quality, longer-life
     gold mining opportunities."

     <h3>The steps being taken are as follows:</h3>

     A preliminary short form prospectus is being filed to offer
     preferred securities for sale in the United States with a term of 49
     years up to an aggregate principal amount of US$300 million.  A
     description of the terms of the preferred securities will be set forth
     in one or more prospectus supplements.
	<p>
     CIBC Wood Gundy Securities Inc. has been retained to assist
     with the sale of a package consisting of the Sigma and Kiena gold
     mines in Val d'Or, Canada, and gold exploration properties in the
     vicinity.
	<p>
    CIBC Wood Gundy Securities Inc. has been retained to assist
      with a review of alternatives for the sale of the Endako molybdenum
     mine in Canada.
	<p>
     Activities at the Detour Lake Mine in Canada are to be heavily
     focused on exploring the QK zone with a view to accelerating its
     development.  Mining of the Main zone will continue on a break-even
     basis to provide the infrastructure and support for QK zone-related
     activities.
	<p>
            Work will be terminated at the Paymaster property adjoining the
     Dome Mine in Canada following completion of an exploration drilling
     and test stoping programme which has concluded that the economics are
     marginal.
	<p>
       	A registration statement relating to the preferred securities will
     be filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  The
     securities may not be sold nor may offers to buy be accepted prior to
     the time the registration statement becomes effective.  This press
     release does not constitute an offer to sell or the solicitation of an
     offer to sell or the solicitation of an offer to buy, nor shall there
     be any sale of the securities in any jurisdiction in which such offer,
     solicitation or sale would be unlawful prior to registration or
     qualification under the securities laws of any such jurisdiction.


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
