    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	<h2>
	Placer Dome seeks partnership with Bre-X Minerals
	</h2>

	<strong>
	December 2, 1996
	</strong>
	<p>    

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. disclosed today that for the past
     two months it has been negotiating specific proposals with Bre-X
     Minerals Ltd. and its advisers for participation in the Busang gold
     property in Indonesia as part of a normal auction process.
     <p>
        As a result of considerable discussion, a conditional offer which
     reflected a price well in excess of today's Bre-X price was discussed,
     and a due diligence property visit was being arranged.  At that point,
     Placer Dome was told by Bre-X that the tendering process had been
     pre-empted.
       <p>
        Placer Dome confirms that it remains keen to acquire a substantial
     interest in Busang and wishes to rapidly develop the property.  The
     Corporation is especially qualified as, employing its own in-house
     capabilities, it has constructed nine mines in the last 11 years, two
     of them in the same challenging tropical environment as Busang.
      <p>
        John Willson, President and Chief Executive Officer, said today:
     "We were very disappointed to see the auction process pre-empted.  We
     regret that the opportunity for Bre-X shareholders to determine the
     value of their holdings, and to exercise their natural right to
     determine their partner, was taken away.
     <p>
        "However, we note that in Thursday's Toronto Globe and Mail
     newspaper, the Indonesian Vice-Consul for Investments, Jean Anes,
     indicated that the Indonesian Government is willing to consider other
     offers before the deadline of December 4.  We have therefore notified
     the Government that Placer Dome is not only highly qualified to
     participate with Bre-X and the Government in the development of Busang
     but wish to make a competitive offer to do so."

	

		<p>
	
	For further information:<br>	
	Investor Relations - Earl Dunlop  (604) 661-3779<br>	
	Media Relations - Hugh Leggatt  (604) 661-1554<br>	
	

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
	
