	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome offers to acquire Highlands Gold
        and the minority of Placer Pacific</h2>
	
    <strong>November 27, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>

        

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces it is launching
     takeover bids for the 24.6% publicly owned interest in its subsidiary
     Placer Pacific Limited, as well as for all of the shares of Highlands
     Gold Limited, a Papua New Guinea company which owns 25% of the Porgera
     Joint Venture.  The value of these transactions upon completion will
     be about US$600 million.
     <p> 
        "This is about growth for Placer Dome shareholders and a golden
     opportunity for the shareholders of Highlands Gold and minority
     shareholders of Placer Pacific," John Willson, President and Chief
     Executive Officer, said.  "We have great confidence in the Asia Pacific
     region.  Placer Dome is consolidating its presence to compete more
     effectively."
     <p> 
        The bid for Highlands Gold is a cash offer of A$0.75 per share.
     The offer will be conditional upon no material change to the business
     or operations of Highlands Gold, the Australian Stock Exchange Gold
     Index not falling below 1500 during the offer period, and the Bank of
     Papua New Guinea approving Papua New Guinea residents' acceptance of
     the offer.  There will be no minimum acceptance condition.
     <p> 
         With on-market purchases made yesterday at A$0.75 per share,
     Placer Dome already holds 33% of Highlands Gold.  Placer Dome is
     making an offer at the same price to all shareholders under the Papua
     New Guinea Companies Act.
     <p> 
         "The offer represents a premium of over 36% on the Highlands Gold
     share price on Tuesday, November 26, the date immediately before
     yesterday's purchases," Mr. Willson said.  "It is cash, it has no
     minimum acceptance condition and I believe that Highlands Gold
     shareholders will recognize the attractiveness of the offer," he said.
     <p> 
        Placer Dome also announces it is offering one Placer Dome common
     share for every 15 Placer Pacific shares.  The bid is conditional upon
     Placer Dome gaining sufficient acceptances to exercise compulsory
     acquisition rights under the Australian Corporations Law, there being
     no material adverse change to the business or operations of Placer
     Pacific, the Australian Stock Exchange Gold Index not falling below
     1500 during the currency of the offer, and Foreign Investment Review
     Board approval.
     <p> 
        At Placer Dome's closing price in New York on November 26, the
     offer values Placer Pacific at A$2.03 per share.
    <p> 
        The Placer Pacific offer is not being registered under the U.S.
     Securities Act of 1933 and no shares will be issued to persons
     resident in the United States.
     <p> 
        "We are offering Placer Pacific shareholders the opportunity to
     participate directly in Placer Dome's global growth," Mr. Willson
     said.
     <p> 
         "As well as a significant premium of almost 50% over the Placer
     Pacific price on November 26, Placer Pacific shareholders will
     participate in a high-growth company with a portfolio of mines in
     Australia, the Pacific, and the Americas.  We hope that they will
     remain long-term shareholders of Placer Dome."
     <p> 
        Placer Dome intends to deliver takeover documents to Highlands Gold
     shortly, and expects to send the offer documents to Highlands Gold
     shareholders in mid-December.
     <p> 
        The Placer Pacific takeover documents will take longer to complete
     because it is a share offer, and will be delivered to the company at
     the end of December.  The offer documents will be forwarded to Placer
     Pacific shareholders in mid-January 1997.
     <p> 
        The Placer Pacific offer will be extended to shares issued under
     the Placer Pacific Executive Option Scheme during the offer period.


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
	
