	<tr>
	<td>

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	<h2>
	Placer Dome to tender Gibraltar interest to Westmin offer
	</h2>

	<strong>
	September 10, 1996
	</strong>
	<p>
	
	(all dollar amounts in U.S. currency)
	<p>
	
	

	

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces its 100%-owned subsidiary Placer Dome 
	Canada Limited has agreed with Westmin Resources Limited of Vancouver to tender 
	Placer Domes 30.8% stake in Gibraltar Mines Limited into a take-over bid being made 
	by Westmin for all of the outstanding shares of Gibraltar, a copper producer.  The 
	agreement contemplates that the Corporations 10,156,101 shares of Gibraltar will be 
	tendered for proceeds of C$8.85 per share in cash and common shares, resulting in a 
	gain of about US$11 million net of taxes and currency translation adjustments.
	<p>
	The consideration will consist of cash or shares, or a combination, as follows: (i) 
	C$8.85 in cash per Gibraltar common share up to a maximum aggregate cash payable to 
	all shareholders of Gibraltar of C$86.6 million; or (ii) 1.18 common shares of 
	Westmin per Gibraltar common share based on a Westmin price of C$7.50 per share.  In 
	the event that all Gibraltar shareholders elect to receive cash, the consideration 
	will be pro-rated as to C$2.50 in cash and 0.847 common shares of Westmin per 
	Gibraltar common share.  Placer Dome has agreed to elect to take its consideration in 
	the form of cash to the fullest extent available.
	<p>
	The agreement is subject to limited confirmatory due diligence and, subject to 
	certain conditions, Placer Dome will have the right to tender its Gibraltar shares 
	into any higher offer that may materialize.  Placer Dome previously announced its 
	intention to sell its interest in Gibraltar as part of its focus on growth in gold 
	production.  John Willson, President and CEO, said: "This is a very good deal for all 
	Gibraltar shareholders and will ensure the Lomas Bayas project can move forward 
	rapidly as part of a company that has a strategic focus on growth in base metal 
	production."
	<p>
	Gibraltar owns and operates the McLeese Lake Mine, an open pit operation producing 
	copper in concentrate and cathode form in British Columbia, and is developing the 
	Lomas Bayas oxide copper deposit in northern Chile.

	

		<p>
	
	For further information:<br>	
	Investor Relations - Earl Dunlop  (604) 661-3779<br>	
	Media Relations - Hugh Leggatt  (604) 661-1554<br>	
	

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
