    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome announces intention to sell 30.8% interest in Gibraltar</h2>
	
    <strong>September 4, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>

     <strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces that its wholly owned
     subsidiary, Placer Dome Canada Limited, has retained Nesbitt Burns
     Inc. to identify strategic buyers for its 30.8% interest in Gibraltar
     Mines Limited.  This step is in keeping with Placer Dome's focus on
     growth in gold.
        <p>
     Gibraltar Mines Limited owns and operates the McLeese Lake copper mine
     near Williams Lake, British Columbia and owns 100% of the Lomas Bayas
     and Fortuna de Cobre oxide copper deposits in Chile.  Gibraltar
     recently announced that it has obtained a bank financing commitment of
     US$140 million for development of the Lomas Bayas project, which
     together with the Fortuna property, has total reserves and geological
     resources of 8.92 billion pounds of contained copper.


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

