	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	<h2>
	Additional ore identified at Porgera
	</h2>
	
	<strong>
	August 12, 1996
	</strong>
	<p>

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc.'s share of proven and probable gold reserves
	at the 18.8%-owned Porgera Mine in Papua New Guinea has increased by 490,000
	ounces to 2.2 million ounces at June 30, 1996, from 1.7 million ounces at the end
	of 1995, as a result of revised estimates by the Porgera Joint Venture (PJV).
	<p>
	Porgera's total proven and probable ore reserves are now estimated to be 78.7
	million tonnes of ore grading 4.5 grams of gold per tonne containing 11.5 million
	ounces of gold, representing an increase in contained gold of 2.6 million ounces
	over the December 1995 estimate.
	<p>
	The Corporation's share of gold estimated to be contained in other mineralized
	material, which is in addition to its share of reserves, is 222,000 ounces, down
	from 359,000 ounces at the end of 1995, as a portion of these resources were moved
	to the ore reserve category.  The PJV said total measured and indicated resources
	at a cut-off grade of 1.5 grams per tonne are estimated to be 16.4 million tonnes
	at 2.2 grams of gold per tonne containing 1.2 million ounces of gold.
	<p>
	The increased estimates are the result of a substantial increase in data obtained
	by exploration drilling since the December 1995 estimates.  Increased reserves
	have resulted primarily from additions to open pit ore while underground reserves
	also increased.  Because of the extreme topography and the mining sequence, the
	open pit part of the deposit is not as extensively drilled as the underground
	mine.  Both open pit and underground areas remain highly prospective and the PJV
	is extending drill coverage as mining provides suitable access.
	<p>
	By Porgera's sixth anniversary of commercial production on September 1, 1996 the
	mine will have produced more than 6 million ounces of gold.
	<p>
	

For further information:<br>
Investor Relations - Earl Dunlop	(604) 661-3779<br>
Media Relations - Hugh Leggatt	(604) 661-1554<br>


	<br><br>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
	
