	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Venezuela gold project shows positive economics</h2>
	
    <strong>March 26, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces that it has completed a positive feasibility study for development of a mine and processing facilities at the 70%-owned Las Cristinas gold property in south-eastern Venezuela.  The study has been delivered to the joint venturers, Corporacin Venezolana de Guayana (CVG) pending a development decision.
<p>
The study estimates that mineable ore reserves contain 8 million ounces of gold in the main Cuatro Muertos and Conductora zones.  At a milling rate of 40,000 tonnes per day, the operation is expected to produce an average of 450,000 ounces of gold per year for 14.5 years at an average cash cost of $205 per ounce and an average total cost of $310 per ounce, both net of copper credits.  The initial capital cost is estimated to be US$565 million, including contingency.
<p>
The open pit mine will operate with conventional truck shovel combinations and a crushing circuit for bedrock will be introduced in year two of operations.  As significant copper occurs with the gold, a copper concentrate containing gold will be produced as well as gold in dor bullion form.  About 60% of total gold production will be contained in concentrate and 40% will be in dor&#233;.
<p>
For environmental and economic reasons, the processing plan includes measures to recover most of the cyanide used to extract gold.  The mine will employ 840 people at start-up and it is anticipated that most will be Venezuelan nationals.
<p>
The Corporation is continuing to work with government authorities in Venezuela to clarify the fiscal and regulatory regime for gold mining investment.  The timing of a development decision is dependent on this clarification.


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
	
