	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	<h2>
	New Placer Dome mine project approved
	</h2>
	
	<strong>
	March 4, 1996
	</strong>
	<p>

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome U.S. Inc., a unit of gold miner Placer Dome Inc.
	of Vancouver, announced today that approvals have been received for development of
	the Pipeline gold deposit at the 60%-owned Cortez Joint Venture, and construction
	of a mill and related facilities will commence immediately.
		<p>
	The Nevada State Office of the Bureau of Land Management (BLM) has issued a formal
	Approval of the Plan of Operations for the Pipeline Project in Crescent Valley,
	Nevada.  The BLM also issued a favourable Record of Decision for the Final
	Environmental Impact Statement (EIS).  The Cortez Joint Venture, owners of the
	Pipeline Project, announced an immediate construction decision.  The joint venture
	is owned by Placer Dome U.S. Inc. and Kennecott Explorations (Australia) Ltd.
	(40%).  Placer Dome U.S. is the operator.  The Pipeline Project is located near
	the existing Cortez gold mine which has been in operation since 1968.
		<p>
	Pipeline will be an open pit gold mine with 4.3 million ounces of gold reserves. 
	The total capital cost to develop the combined carbon-in-leach mill and heap leach
	facility is estimated to be US$319 million.  Output is planned to average about
	310,000 ounces of gold per year for 12 years.  Construction and commissioning will
	take place over a 15-month period with production to begin in mid-1997.
		<p>
	Jay K. Taylor, President and CEO of Placer Dome U.S., said: "Pipeline is a great
	project which will be a significant part of Placer Dome U.S. for many years."  He
	acknowledged that the 41-month permitting process was arduous but comprehensive. 
	"Although it has been a difficult process at times, we would like to acknowledge
	the effort of the BLM in completing a professional and comprehensive EIS," Taylor
	said.
		<p>
	Placer Dome U.S. currently operates two gold mines in Nevada and one in Montana
	and conducts active exploration projects throughout the U.S. and Mexico.
		<p>
	
	For further information:<br>	
	Placer Dome U.S. Inc. - Joe Danni  (415) 397-7237<br>
	Investor Relations - Earl Dunlop  (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations - Hugh Leggatt  (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
	
