	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Placer Dome announces senior management change</h2>
	
    <strong>January 3, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Domes 75%-owned subsidiary, Placer Pacific Limited, announced today that as a result of the resignation of its Managing Director, Lawrie Reinertson, it will appoint Dick Zandee, 50, to that position before the end of the first quarter of 1996.  The timing will accommodate a smooth transition between Mr. Reinertson and Mr. Zandee.
<p>
Mr. Reinertson has notified Placer Pacific that he is leaving to become President and Chief Executive Officer of Rio Algom Limited, a mineral producer based in Toronto.  He joined the Placer Dome Group as Senior Vice-President, Exploration, based in Vancouver, in 1987 and became Managing Director of Placer Pacific and Kidston Gold Mines Limited in 1990.
<p>
Since joining Placer Pacific, he has led the Company to record earnings over four successive years.  It is with great regret that his resignation has been accepted by the Placer Pacific Board of Directors and he will leave with the gratitude and best wishes of his fellow Directors and employees.
<p>
Mr. Zandee, a mining engineer, has been with the Placer Dome Group for 27 years and has broad experience in international operations in Canada, the Philippines and Papua New Guinea.  He is currently Managing Director of Placer Niugini Limited, based in Port Moresby.  His extensive mining background and depth of experience, especially in Papua New Guinea, make him eminently qualified to lead Placer Pacific.


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
    </td>
