	<tr>
	<td>
	

    <br>
    <a href="09c.html">Back to "Current News Releases"</a>
    
    <p>

	
    <h2>Marcopper accident to reduce Placer Dome earnings</h2>
	
    <strong>June 27, 1996</strong>
    
    <p>

	<strong>Vancouver, Canada</strong> - Placer Dome Inc. announces that it will be recording a US$40 million after tax provision against second quarter earnings as a result of the accidental escape of tailing (ground-up rock and water) at the 40%-owned Marcopper Mine in the Philippines.
<p>
The provision reflects the Corporations conclusion that, as a result of the accident and the subsequent revocation of its Environmental Compliance Certificate, Marcopper may be unable to repay the US$21 million of its loans guaranteed by Placer Dome, or to pay US$4 million of amounts due to Placer Dome.  The provision includes an amount of US$15 million representing the Corporations recently completed estimate of the net cost of repairing the drainage tunnel through which the tailing escaped, and mitigating the environmental impacts of the accident.
<p>
John Willson, President and Chief Executive Officer, said: "Placer Dome has repeatedly expressed regret for what happened and we have made firm commitments to the Government of the Philippines that we will act responsibly and mitigate the effects of this unfortunate accident.  In this spirit, Placer Dome has devised engineering solutions to repair the tunnel, and we have a plan awaiting government approval for dredging of the river mouth to mitigate potential future flooding.  With our support, Marcopper has built flood protection and housing on higher ground for river-bank residents, and has organized community support services.
<p>
"This significant provision against earnings reflects our determination to carry through the necessary work, despite Marcoppers current lack of cash flow.  Given the importance we attach to our environmental record, we are prepared to go beyond our obligations as a 40% shareholder of Marcopper."


    
    <p>

	
	For further information:<br>
    Investor Relations: Earl Dunlop (604) 661-3779<br>
	Media Relations: Hugh Leggatt (604) 661-1554<br>

	<br><br>
    
