<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>36th Annual CGS Presentation/San Francisco</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<Body background=/images/back1.gif>
<BR><H2><Center>36th Annual CGS Presentation/San Francisco</Center></H2>
<P>
<img src="/images/new.gif"><P>
<B>Three options are available to download the presentation.</b>
<P>
<ul>
<li>For PC users with MS PowerPoint 7.0, download and unzip
<a href="cgs7.zip">cgs7.zip (391 kb)</a>. Load the file <B>cgs7.ppt</B> into
PowerPoint.<P>

<li>For PC users with MS PowerPoint 4.0, download and unzip
<a href="cgs4.zip">cgs4.zip (110 kb)</a>. Load the file <B>cgs4.ppt</B> into
PowerPoint.
<P>
<li>For PC users without MS PowerPoint, download and run the program
<a href="grad.exe">grad.exe (915 kb)</a>. This will extract the presentation
and the viewer. Next, run the program <B>prgsetup.exe</B> to view the presentation.
</ul>


<img src=/images/hline.gif><P> 
<h6>This page has been enhanced for use with
<A href="http://www.netscape.com">
Netscape Navigator 1.1N</A></h6><P>
<h6>Last Modified: <I>January 8, 1997</I></h6>
<p>
If you have problems, questions, or suggestions concerning our
server, please contact:<p> 
<A HREF="mailto:ddiane@clemson.edu">
