<html><head><title>Clemson Grad School Electronic Application
Instructions</title></head>
<body>
<Center><h2>Electronic Application Instructions for<br>
U.S. Citizens or Permanent Residents</h2>
<B>
Clemson University Graduate School</B></center><P>



Instead of completing a paper application form, you may choose to
transmit your application
to Clemson University via the Internet.  If you choose the paper
application option, please proceed to 
<a href="request.htm"><B>REQUEST FOR INFORMATION</B></a>.
If you are an international student and wish to apply
electronically, please see <a href="int_in.htm">Admission
Information for International Students.</A>

<P>
<B>PLEASE NOTE:</b> The Graduate School recommends you use the
<b>Netscape 
Navigator</b> browser version <b>1.1N</b> or newer with our
application. If your 
browser will not handle our application, you may 
<a href="http://home.netscape.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">
download</a>  
the latest version of Netscape.

<blockquote>

You must complete all information on the application form.
Your application cannot be processed until it is complete.
<P>
<a href="instr.htm#Transcripts">
Transcripts</a>,
<a href="instr.htm#Letters"> 
letters of recommendation</a>
and 
<a href="instr.htm#Fee">
application fee payment</a>
must be sent via U.S. mail in one envelope.  Your application
will
not be considered
complete until all the relevant items have been received.  Do not
open envelopes with
transcripts or letters of recommendation after they are sent to
you.  Include them in one
envelope and mail to the Graduate School.
<a name="Fee">
<P>
</a>

<B>APPLICATION FEE.
A $35 nonrefundable</B> application fee payable to Clemson University via
money order or a check drawn on a U.S. bank, is required. If you apply to a
second program, you do not need to pay an additional fee. If you apply
to more than two programs, each program after the second will require an
additional $35 fee. The application fee(s) must be received before the
application will be processed. <B>Application fee(s) cannot be waived or
deferred.</B> Applications received electronically will be discarded after
60 days if application fee is not received.


<a name="Transcripts">
<P>
</a>
<B>TRANSCRIPTS.</B> Two official transcripts from all previously
attended colleges
and/or universities are required.  You may omit any colleges
and/or universities where
insignificant or nonrelevant course work was taken.  Please
request that the registrar's office
at each institution give you official transcripts of your
academic work in sealed envelope(s)
with official signature over seal.  Refer to <a
href="trans.htm">Request Form</a>.
<P>
<a name="Test">
<B>TEST SCORES.</B>  Scores must be sent directly from
Educational Testing Service or from the Psychological
Corporation, and such
scores must not be older than five years relative to the date of
acceptance.
<a name="Letters">
<P>
</a>
<B>LETTERS OF RECOMMENDATION.</B>  At least two letters of
recommendation are
required for admission to certain programs.  
Please
request that the recommenders complete the <a
href="recomm.htm">Recommendation
Form</a> and return them to you in sealed envelopes.
<P>
<B>MAILING INSTRUCTIONS.</B>  Mail all required materials,
including application fee,
to: 
<blockquote>Graduate School<br>
Clemson University<br> 
E-108 Martin Hall<br> 
Box 345120<br>
Clemson, SC  29634-5120.  
</blockquote>
Forms that are provided in electronic format are to be printed
from 
your browser.



</blockquote>
<P>
<hr size-4>
<P>
If you are ready to complete the electronic application, click
<B>APPLY</B>.
If you would like to preview a sample application, click
<B>PREVIEW</A>.
<P>
