<hr>
<P>
South Carolina, with its long and distinguished history, is a state that looks
to the future. In providing a variety of opportunities for its citizens to 
prosper and enjoy their quality of life, the state has achieved a diversified
economy and has made great strides in educational opportunities, largely
through an emphasis on technology, support for research and a close,
cooperative relationship between business/industry and higher education.<P>
<P>
South Carolina is broadly divided into three regions: the Coastal Plain, the
Midlands and the Piedmont/mountain region of the Upstate, where Clemson
University is located. Historic cities, beautiful gardens, the scenic Atlantic
coast, and the state's lakes and mountains provide recreational opportunities
from coast to border. State parks are located throughout the state and are
popular vacation spots year-round. From the Blue Ridge Mountains to historic
Charleston, South Carolina is a truly delightful place to live, work and
study.<P>
<P>
Clemson is located in South Carolina's lake and mountain region. An interstate
highway system is located near the town, and railway and air travel are both
accessible.<P>
     <P>
     <P>
     <P></dl>
<A HREF="http://www.grad.clemson.edu/page1.htm"><IMG SRC=/images/back.gif></A>

