<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>College of Agriculture, Foresty and Life Sciences</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background=/images/back1.gif>
<A NAME=QuickMark></A><P>
<a href="http://agweb.clemson.edu/">
<B><H2>College of Agriculture, Forestry and Life Sciences</B></H2></a><P>

<table cellpadding=20>
<th>P=Professional Master's<th>M=Traditional Master's       
<th>D=Doctorate<tr>
</table>

Traditional master's degrees are the MA and MS degrees.  GRE general test scores are
required for admission unless indicated otherwise.  A minimum of 30 semester hours of
graduate credit is required for the degrees.
<P>
Doctoral programs require GRE general test scores for admission. A minimum of 18 hours of
dissertation research is required.
<P>

<B>Agricultural and Applied Economics (M)</B>   
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Students interested in the PhD
program should see the applied economics program.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Agricultural Education (P)</B>    
<BLOCKQUOTE>Degree is Master of Agricultural Education (MAgEd). Students
interested in the doctoral program should apply to vocational/technical
education program in the College of Health, Education and Human
Development.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Agricultural Engineering (P,M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE> Professional degree is Master of Engineering (MEngr). MS thesis
required. Additional 36 hours of course work beyond the
masters's degree and 18 hours of dissertation research are 
required. All programs offered jointly with the College
of Engineering and Science.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B><A HREF="http://agweb.clemson.edu/">Agriculture (P)</A></B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Degree is Master of Agriculture (MAg); concentrations are in 
agricultural economics, agricultural mechanization and business, animal industries and plant
health;

 GRE scores required for admission for
applicants lacking postbaccalaureate professional experience.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Agronomy (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis and nonthesis options are available; nonthesis
option intended as terminal degree. Possession of master's
degree, with thesis, highly recommended for PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Animal and Food Industries (M)</B>
<UL>
<LI>Animal, Dairy and Veterinary Sciences
<LI>Food Science
<LI><A HREF="http://agweb.clemson.edu/poultry/poultry.htm">Poultry Science</A>
</UL><BLOCKQUOTE>Concentrations are in the departments listed; MS thesis
required.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Animal Physiology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Possession of master's degree highly
recommended for PhD applicants. Both programs draw on faculty from the
Departments of Biological Sciences; Animal, Dairy and
Veterinary Sciences; Food Science; Poultry Science; and Aquaculture, 
Fisheries and Wildlife.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Applied Economics (D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Offered cooperatively by the Department of Economics in the
College of Business and Public Affairs and the Department of Agricultural and Applied 
Economics; possession of master's degree preferred for admission.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Aquaculture, Fisheries &amp; Wildlife Biology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. PhD program requires approximately 30 semester
hours of graduate course work, one semester of professional experience and 18 hours of
dissertation research.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Biochemistry (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Possession of MS degree not a prerequisite for
PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Botany (M)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Students interested in PhD studies should
apply to the plant physiology program.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>
<A HREF="http://biowww.clemson.edu/ento/home.html">Entomology (M,D)</A></B> 


<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Possession of master's degree highly
recommended for PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Environmental Toxicology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Possession of master's degree recommended for
PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B><A HREF="http://agweb.clemson.edu/Hort/HortMain.htm">Food Technology
(D)</A></B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Possession of master's degree highly recommended.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Forest Resources (P,M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Professional degree is Master of Forest Resources (MFR) requiring 36
hours.  MS thesis required. PhD degree requires a minimum of 16 hours of course work and
18 hours of research.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Genetics (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. PhD degree requires a minimum of 24 hours of course
work beyond the
BS degree and 18 hours of dissertation research.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B><A HREF="http://agweb.clemson.edu/Hort/HortMain.htm">Horticulture (M)</A></B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Students interested in PhD studies should
apply to the plant physiology program.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Microbiology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. PhD program requires 18 hours of dissertation
research; possession of MS degree desirable for PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Nutrition (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis and nonthesis options are available. Possession of
master's degree highly recommended for PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Plant Pathology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis required. Possession of master's degree highly
recommended for PhD applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B><A HREF="http://agweb.clemson.edu/Hort/HortMain.htm">Plant Physiology
(D)</A></B>
<BLOCKQUOTE> Interdisciplinary program with the Departments of Agronomy, Biological
Sciences, Forest Resources, Horticulture, and Plant
Pathology &amp Physiology; possession of master's degree highly
recommended.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Zoology (M,D)</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>MS thesis and nonthesis options are available; nonthesis option requires
36 hours of course work; Possession of MS degree not necessary for PhD
applicants.</BLOCKQUOTE>
