AP EC 804	APPLIED MATHEMATICAL ECONOMICS
(ECON 804)	3 cr. (3 and 0)
	Mathematical tools needed in economic analysis. Topics include matrix algebra, differentiation, 
unconstrained and constrained optimization, integration and linear programming.

AP EC 806	ECONOMETRICS I
(ECON 806)	3 cr. (3 and 0)
	Application of econometric techniques and stochastic models to economic problems. Topics 
include distribution theory, simple and multiple regression modeling, hypothesis testing and 
other issues in regression analysis.

