<h1>Engineering Graphics</h1>
William F. Beckwith, Program Director, Freshman Engineering and
Engineering Graphics
<P>
Advanced degrees are not awarded in engineering graphics. Courses
are offered as electives for students in engineering and other
areas.
<P>
<PRE>
E G 612   INTERACTIVE COMPUTER GRAPHICS
     3 cr. (3 and 0)

E G 690   SPECIAL TOPICS IN ENGINEERING AND COMPUTER GRAPHICS
     1-3 cr.

E G 823   COMPUTER-AIDED GEOMETRIC MODELING
     3 cr. (3 and 0)
     Shape modeling and design by computer; curve and surface
representation, methods of solid modeling by computer; data base
representation and integral properties of solid models.
Prerequisite: Graduate standing.
